comments: Zubac (LAC) establishes himself in a screening position in Okoro's (CLE) path and absorbs the contact during the screen.
Batum (LAC) is in the paint and actively guarding an opponent within three seconds.
Zubac (LAC) avoids making contact with Garland's (CLE) head as he contests the shot near the rim and Batum (LAC) cleanly blocks the shot.
Batum (LAC) fumbles the rebound and loses control of the ball out of bounds. Possession is correctly awarded to Cleveland.
Mann (LAC) and Garland (CLE) mutually engage and marginal contact occurs as Mann's hand gets caught briefly in Garland's jersey. Garland then secures the inbound pass as they disengage.
Okoro (CLE) brings his arm forward towards Kennard's (LAC) front and marginal contact occurs as they disengage.
Kennard (LAC) receives the pass on his left foot and establishes his right as his pivot, when he then lifts and re-plants prior to starting his dribble.
Okoro (CLE) extends his leg into Kennard's (LAC) path and makes contact with his lower body, which affects his SQBR.
Mobley (CLE) and Zubac (LAC) briefly engage and disengage during the inbound.
Mobley (CLE) jumps and brushes Zubac's (LAC) back and marginal contact occurs as Zubac spins towards the opposite side of the rim.
Zubac (LAC) is already in Garland's (CLE) path and is firming up when contact occurs.

Replay review of the foul called on Garland (CLE) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Garland (CLE) moves laterally in Coffey's (LAC) path and initiates contact that affects his SQBR. While Coffey has not yet gathered the ball when the contact occurs, the Clippers are in the bonus and correctly receive two free throws.
Zubac (LAC) briefly grasps and immediately releases Mobley's (CLE) arm as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Zubac's (LAC) tip-shot attempt hits the wiring above the basket and is correctly called out of bounds. Cleveland is correctly awarded possession.
Zubac (LAC) straddles the lane line and is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
LeVert (CLE) has his leg planted and is established in Coffey's (LAC) path when incidental leg to leg contact occurs as he retreats alongside Coffey's path.
LeVert (CLE) legally contests Coffey's (LAC) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Kennard (LAC) is already in Markkanen's (CLE) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
LeVert (CLE) makes contact with Zubac's (LAC) arm, which affects his shot near the rim.
Zubac (LAC) jumps forward into Okoro (CLE) and initiates contact that affects his shot near the rim.
Batum (LAC) is already in Okoro's (CLE) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Markkanen (CLE) rests his hands on Hartenstein's (LAC) back and marginal contact occurs as he releases for the rebound that goes over their heads.
Batum (LAC) moves slightly forward towards Garland (CLE) and marginal contact occurs as Garland pivots away from Batum.
Garland's (CLE) foot comes down in the backcourt before he releases his pass.
Kennard (LAC) turns away from LeVert (CLE) and marginal contact occurs as they come together during the drive.
Mobley (CLE) is in the lane for longer than three seconds.
Garland (CLE) legally contests Mann's (LAC) jump shot attempt.

As Hartenstein (LAC) tips the ball his forearm makes contact with Mobley's (CLE) head during his follow through, which causes Mobley to momentarily lose control of the ball before he regains possession.   Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Kennard (LAC) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Hartenstein (LAC) brings his arm down and makes contact with Markkanen's (CLE) arm, which affects his play at the basket.
Okoro (CLE) is established in a legal guarding position in Batum's (LAC) path and absorbs the marginal contact initiated by Batum during the jump shot attempt.
